      <bioghist id="aspace_609710857c57960d0d2c2ce7ff80a907">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Big Ox Mining and Reduction Company was incorporated in Helena, Montana Territory, in 1889 to mine the Marysville-Silver Creek Mining District. In 1896, John W. Fulton, Charles J. Fulton (1848-1928), and M. A. H. Fulton purchased the mining properties of the Big Ox Mining and Reduction Company, renamed the company Big Ox Mining Company, and operated the Big Ox Mine and Golconda Mine until about 1916. The company went bankrupt in 1926; the Fultons continued to purchase and operate properties until the mid-1930s.</p>  
      </bioghist>
